            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Merchynt Paige</td>
              <td>$99/mo</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Yes (specialist)</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>GBP only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Alli AI</td>
              <td>$299/mo</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Yes (mass edits)</td>
              <td>On-page at scale</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Surfer SEO</td>
              <td>$89/mo</td>
              <td>No (manual)</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Content scoring</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Local Falcon</td>
              <td>$24/mo</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Tracking only</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>GBP rank tracking</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Journalist AI</td>
              <td>$39/mo</td>
              <td>Yes</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>News publishing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Diib</td>
              <td>$14.99/mo</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Monitoring only</td>
              <td>Growth guidance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>BrightLocal</td>
              <td>$39/mo</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Partial</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Citations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Autoblogging.ai</td>
              <td>$29/mo</td>
              <td>Yes (bulk)</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Volume publishing</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BUYER'S GUIDE -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-inner">
      <div class="problem-label">How to choose</div>
      <h2 class="problem-heading">Which AI SEO agent fits your situation?</h2>

      <div class="ba-grid">
        <div class="ba-col before">
          <div class="ba-col-label">Small business or local service</div>
          <p class="ba-body">
            <strong>theStacc</strong> is the clear choice. It's the only agent built for businesses without a marketing team — it handles content publishing, GBP management, and social distribution in one subscription. No technical setup, no ongoing management, no VA required.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="ba-col after">
          <div class="ba-col-label">Established site with technical debt</div>
          <p class="ba-body">
            <strong>Search Atlas OTTO or Alli AI</strong> are worth the higher price point. If your site has thousands of pages with inconsistent metadata, broken schema, or crawl issues, autonomous technical SEO agents pay for themselves quickly — especially if you'd otherwise need a developer.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ba-grid">
        <div class="ba-col before">
          <div class="ba-col-label">GBP-focused local business</div>
          <p class="ba-body">
            <strong>theStacc</strong> includes GBP management as part of its full-stack agent. If you need GBP-only automation and already have content handled, <strong>Merchynt Paige</strong> is the most specialized option. For rank tracking specifically, <strong>Local Falcon</strong> is unmatched on geo-grid visualization.
          </p>
